fields.value: 3D Model of Egyptian Votive Box EA27584

dsDescriptionValue.value:
Photogrammetric model of copper alloy votive box (British Museum EA27584).

Description: Hollow-cast, copper alloy votive box, also known as relic-box or animal coffin; rectangular case surmounted by two solid-cast figures of lizards lying side by side; one eyelet for suspension between them; very corroded with some elements of burnt clay visible in the corrosion; surface slightly blackened, possibly burnt; case complete, should contain a mummified lizard or two (or parts of). (Taken from British Museum webpage: https://www.britishmuseum.org/research/collection_online/collection_object_details.aspx?objectId=149902&partId=1)

88 photos taken using a Sony Xperia X Compact. 3D model created in Agisoft Photoscan. Data in OBJ format, with associated JPEG texture file and MTL file.

Data © Trustees of the British Museum
